The Face of Ilaji Beauty Pageant has resumed for the 2021 edition. The entry for the first edition has opened for healthy, intelligent, and decent Nigerian girls from 18 to 28 years who will contest for the prestigious Face of Ilaji crown. The pageantâ€™s Coordinator, Umar Kashim, in a statement, said the pageant is unique in the sense that the platform will also empower contestants by equipping them with business skills using the Ilaji business model as created by Chief Dotun Sanusi, an engineer. Umar said the beauty pageant would also help to bring out the best in young Nigeria women by building their self-confidence, personal development and increase their drive for success. The offline and online audition of the pageant is scheduled to begin on May 15, 2021.